<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-03-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-03-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="19" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d19">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Koerner</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 74.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-03-22"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 22, 1864</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi>For your information I enclose herewith a
                            copy of a despatch of the 12th instant from the consulate general at
                            Havana, on the subject of an apprehended revolt of the negroes on the
                            island, through the agency of Dominican and Haytian emissaries.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Gustavus Koerner</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Madrid.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>